The eight major New York City banks haddaily average borrowings of 169 mln dlrs from the FederalReserve in the week ended April 8, a Fed spokesman said.    A Fed spokesman said that all of the borrowings were madeyesterday by fewer than half the banks.    It was the second half of the two-week bank statementperiod that ended on Wednesday. Average borrowings by thesebanks were 142 mln dlrs in the first week of the period.    Reuter&#3;